@page "/projects"
@using MudBlazor

<PageTitle>Projects</PageTitle>

<MudContainer MaxWidth="MaxWidth.Large" Class="mt-4">
    <MudStack Spacing="3">
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h4">Projects</MudText>
        <MudCard>
            <MudCardHeader>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">EvoEnergy Eim Project</MudText>
                <MudChipSet T="string" Class="mt-1">
                    <MudChip Color="Color.Primary" Variant="Variant.Outlined" Label="true">Blazor</MudChip>
                    <MudChip Color="Color.Primary" Variant="Variant.Outlined" Label="true">C#</MudChip>
                    <MudChip Color="Color.Secondary" Variant="Variant.Outlined" Label="true">Web development</MudChip>
                </MudChipSet>
            </MudCardHeader>
        </MudCard>
        <MudCardContent>
            <MudText Class="highlight">
                During my placement year at EvoEnergy, I worked on a web application to help manage and visualise energy data for clients. The application was built using Blazor and C#, allowing for a seamless integration with existing systems.
            </MudText>
            <MudText Class="highlight">
                My role involved both front-end and back-end development, ensuring that the user interface was intuitive while also handling complex data processing tasks. This project provided me with valuable experience in full-stack web development and working in a professional environment.
            </MudText>
        </MudCardContent>
        <!-- Necopinatus -->
        <MudCard>
            <MudCardHeader>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">Necopinatus</MudText>
                <MudChipSet T="string" Class="mt-1">
                    <MudChip Color="Color.Primary" Variant="Variant.Outlined" Label="true">Unity</MudChip>
                    <MudChip Color="Color.Primary" Variant="Variant.Outlined" Label="true">C#</MudChip>
                    <MudChip Color="Color.Secondary" Variant="Variant.Outlined" Label="true">Team project</MudChip>
                </MudChipSet>
            </MudCardHeader>
            <MudCardContent>
                <MudText Class="highlight">
                    Necopinatus is a Unity-based game created in my second year of university alongside a group of five other students from different courses. Together we created this product and won a competition between the other students.
                </MudText>

                <!-- Video -->
                <div class="media-wrap mt-2">
                    <video src="media/Necopinatus_Trailer.mp4" controls></video>
                </div>
            </MudCardContent>
        </MudCard>

        <!-- Zool -->
        <MudCard>
            <MudCardHeader>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">Zool</MudText>
                <MudChipSet T="string" Class="mt-1">
                    <MudChip Color="Color.Primary" Variant="Variant.Outlined" Label="true">Vulkan</MudChip>
                    <MudChip Color="Color.Primary" Variant="Variant.Outlined" Label="true">DX11 → Vulkan</MudChip>
                    <MudChip Color="Color.Secondary" Variant="Variant.Outlined" Label="true">Porting</MudChip>
                </MudChipSet>
            </MudCardHeader>
            <MudCardContent>
                <MudText Class="highlight">
                    In my final year I worked with fellow students to port the game <em>Zool</em> from Windows DX11 to Vulkan so it could be used on the Nintendo Switch when a development kit becomes available.
                </MudText>
                <MudText Class="highlight">
                    This project was licensed to our group by Sumo Digital, who wanted both an Orbis port and a Vulkan port of their license <em>Zool</em>. I enjoyed working within a team immensely.
                </MudText>

                <MudPaper Elevation="0" Class="mt-2">
                    <MudImage Src="images/zool_menu.png" Alt="Zool menu" Class="gallery-img" />
                </MudPaper>
            </MudCardContent>
        </MudCard>
    </MudStack>
</MudContainer>